RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 45. Maiden Claiming Purse 21200. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELLIES AT WINDSOR took a quick lead and rated the pace inside, came under pressure approaching the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and was steadily handled in the lane. ODINA rated close inside on the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and settled for second best. ISLE BE THERE was bumped leaving the gate and raced well back inside on the first turn, eased out leaving the turn, bid toward the three eighths pole, raced in the five path of the far turn and came along for third inside the sixteenth pole. AFLEET PENGUIN lost ground into the first turn and rounded the turn about the four path, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the four path of the far turn then flattened in the lane. AWESOME MOON stalked the early pace three wide, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then weakened into the lane. GOLDEN SALLY ducked out and made contact with Isle Be There leaving the gate, was forced to the five path on the first turn and left the turn outside, bid approaching the three eighths pole but flattened in the three path of the far turn. ONLY ROMANCE stalked the early pace two deep, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Odina
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,chased 3/8,off rail far turn,settled 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Ellies At Windsor
ENTRY.COMMENT: quick lead,rated pace,pressured 3/8,rail far turn,held well drvng

ENTRY.NAME: Isle Be There
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,well back inside,bid 3/8,5p far turn,along 3rd 1/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 90. Starter Allowance Purse 23000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE FEBRUARY 11, 2021. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 11 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since December 11 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DULCIMER DAME took the lead and moved to the inside to rate the pace, was given rein to keep ahead of VOLNAY leaving the three eighths pole, raced clear of that one midway on the far turn then kept alert through the lane. The latter tapered in and raced with the pace two deep, dueled from the three eighths pole but dropped back off the rail midway on the far turn, was steadily handled leaving the turn and held on for second. DIVINE FASHION rounded the opening turn in the five path, gave chase into the backstretch and raced near the rail on the far turn, then outfinished in the stretch duel for second. SHERIFF'S KID saved ground just off the early pace, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, came through the far turn in the three and four paths then flattened in the lane. SWEET ANNABELLA rounded the opening turn about the four path, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and weakened in the stretch. MINER'S GEM stumbled to her nose leaving the gate and dropped well back to save ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Dulcimer Dame
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated slim lead inside,given rein 3/8,clear mid turn,kept sharp

ENTRY.NAME: Volnay
ENTRY.COMMENT: with pace 2d,dueled from 3/8,dropped back mid turn,held on 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 13300. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: I B NASTY saved ground well off the early pace, started a bid leaving the half mile pole and circled rivals in the six path of the far turn, dug in for the lead mid-stretch and determinedly eked out the advantage over the stretch challenge of LADY WHISTLEDOWN, who exchanged contact with Brandyurafinegirl leaving the gate and rounded the opening turn in the four path, contested even terms in the three path on the far turn but was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. IRISH SAMURAI raced outside early then angled in on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path and relented in the duel through the stretch. SUPERSNAKE rated close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, contested at a close disadvantage nearest the rail on the far turn and remained a factor to late stretch before flattening stride. ULTIMATE BREEZE rounded the opening turn in the five path, bid nearing the three eighths pole and raced close four wide on the far turn, but flattened inside the eighth pole. PRETTY SPECTACULAR took the early lead at the rail into the first turn, was met at the nine sixteenths pole and gave chase into the backstretch, rounded the far turn near the rail and showed little more. MAYSVILLE MISS raced with the early pace in the three path, took the lead at the nine sixteenths pole and rated on the front end from that point, contested the edge at the rail on the far turn but was met toward mid-stretch and weakened. BRANDYURAFINEGIRL exchanged contact with Lady Whistledown leaving the gate and raced off the rail on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened off the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Supersnake
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close,off rail,chased 7/16,rail far turn,flattened late

ENTRY.NAME: Maysville Miss
ENTRY.COMMENT: with early pace 3p,up 9/16,edge off rail far turn,met 1/16,weaken

ENTRY.NAME: Irish Samurai
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W
ENTRY.COMMENT: outside early,angled in 5/8,chased 3/8,3p far turn,relented lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 90. Starter Allowance Purse 23000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE FEBRUARY 11, 2021. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 11 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since December 11 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COMPANY CLOWN chased through the backstretch and raced close in the three path of the turn, drifted leaving the turn but dug in determinedly to take over past the sixteenth pole and held off the game challenge of KUKULKAN, who gave chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn, eased out leaving the turn and dueled gamely to the finish. GOLDEN G gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn in the three and four paths then dueled through the stretch for third. E J'S REVENGE chased outside, rounded the turn about the six path then outfinished in the stretch duel for third. NITRO TIME came away sharply and set a pressured pace, rounded the turn at the rail, was met mid-stretch and relented later yards. RULING chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and flattened from mid-stretch. BLACK CANDY saved ground in an even effort.

ENTRY.NAME: Kukulkan
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,rail turn,eased out 1/8,game stretch try

ENTRY.NAME: Nitro Time
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,met past 1/16,relented later yards

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 50. Maiden Claiming Purse 13300. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALL THE WAY MAE dropped well back from early contention, started a long steady bid leaving the three eighths pole and circled rivals in the four path of the far turn, took the lead mid-stretch and drew off the final sixteenth. CAN'T FIGURE saved ground on the first turn, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and took aim in the three path of the far turn then dueled through the stretch for second. KERFORD'S COMMISH raced in the four path the first turn then stalked into the backstretch, challenged leaving the seven sixteenths pole, took the lead at the three eighths, rounded the far turn off the rail, drifted leaving the turn, was caught mid-stretch and flattened stride. UNBRIDLED IRISH became a bit edgy in the gate then took the lead nearing the three quarter pole, was met at the seven sixteenths, gave chase leaving the three eighths, but dropped back approaching the quarter pole and weakened. MO STYLISH rated close inside on the opening turn then faded through the backstretch. I'M SO EXTRA settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole but faded at the rail on the far turn. SUNSET QUEEN saved ground on the first turn then eased out with a bid into the backstretch and showed little response.

ENTRY.NAME: All the Way Mae
ENTRY.OWNER: Deiter Kelly Lynn and T J Albert Racing LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: well back early,long steady bid from 3/8,4p turn,up 1/16,drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Sunset Queen
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground 1st turn,eased out chased 1/2,little response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 88. Starter Allowance Purse 24000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE FEBRUARY 11, 2021. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since December 11 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races W here Entered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMPROBABLE STORY rated a slim lead inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn and was steadily handled to widen. JAMMIN JIMTOWN rated close inside, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail, eased outward toward the head of the lane and dueled through the stretch for second. SHANGHAI CANDY saved ground early and settled off the pace, picked up the chase leaving the half mile pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and was outfinished in the stretch duel for second. ALBERTANO rounded the first turn about the four path then saved some ground into the second turn, bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and finished evenly to improve his position. GOLDEN APPEAL stalked the earlier pace from the three path, gave chase leaving the half mile pole, rounded the far turn in the four and five paths and flattened late yards. HONOR THE FLEET raced off the pace about the four path, drew close into the backstretch and challenged at the three eighths pole, but dropped back approaching the eighth pole and weakened. JAMMIN STILL raced off the rail on the first turn then eased out into the backstretch, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the six path and showed little in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Jammin Jimtown
ENTRY.OWNER: A and B Racing Stable LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Improbable Story
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated slim lead inside,pressured 3/8,edge rail turn,widened drvng

ENTRY.NAME: Jammin Still
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,eased out 1/2,chased 7/16,6p far turn,little lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Purse 33900. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 11 A llowed 2 lbs. A Race Since December 11 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GHOSTLY SQUALL set a pressured pace, kept the edge off the rail on the turn, raced clear mid-stretch and was steadily handled to widen the final sixteenth. UNLOCK broke outward and made contact with Merci Road leaving the gate and was pinched back on the chute, picked up the chase outside, rounded the turn off the rail, was bumped off stride nearing mid-stretch but dug in to take second under the wire. SHUTUPN'KISSME broke in and made contact with Merci Road then pressured the pace inside, raced close at the rail on the turn but dropped back toward the sixteenth pole and was nipped from second under the wire. DEEMED ESSENTIAL chased through the backstretch, raced in the four path on the turn, was bumped in and into Unlock in the vicinity of the eighth pole and not encouraged the remainder of the stretch. SISTER JOANN pressured the pace while between horses down the backstretch, dropped back approaching the quarter pole, rounded the turn in the three path, was roughed off the heels of rivals past the eighth pole and not encouraged further. MERCI ROAD was bumped leaving the gate then gave chase, came through the turn five wide, fell with a fatal injury past the eighth pole and had to be euthanized on the track.

ENTRY.NAME: Shutupn'kissme
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in,bumped,pressed pace,close rail turn,nipped 2nd wire

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 16900. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE AUGUST 11, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since August 11 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ MICHELLE'S WAY tapered in to take the lead nearing the three quarter pole and rated the pace inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths, contested the edge nearest the rail on the far turn, drew clear past the eighth pole and held well under steady handling. MARKETABILITY raced well off the early pace toward the inside then eased out with a bid into the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path, dug in leaving the turn, came between horses mid-stretch and dueled through the final sixteenth for second. CHINA CAT rounded the opening turn in the four path, bid leaving the three eighths pole and contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the far turn then dueled through the stretch for third while outfinished for second. CLEARLY VISIBLE saved ground on the first turn then eased out into the backstretch, bid nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced close near the rail on the far turn then outfinished in the stretch duel for third. RAVENEL raced well back inside on the first turn then angled out with a bid into the backstretch, rounded the far turn in the four and five paths and ran evenly down the lane. TORCH CARRIER saved ground into the first turn, bid leaving the three eighths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn, then flattened in the lane. LIGHTFOOT MISS settled in the three path the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and passed rivals. TEMPORARILY saved ground into the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole, steadied at the rail approaching the quarter pole, though came back to finish evenly. SOCIAL EXCLUSION rated close in the two and three paths on the opening turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole but faded off the rail on the far turn. LADY KAZA rated close off the rail on the first turn, gave chase toward the three eighths pole but gave way approaching the five sixteenths.

ENTRY.NAME: Ravenel
ENTRY.COMMENT: well back early,angled out bid 1/2,4& 5p far turn,evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Lady Kaza
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close off rail,chased 3/8,gave way near 5/16

ENTRY.NAME: Marketability
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off pace inside,eased out,bid 1/2,3p far turn,dueled 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: China Cat
